  "prompt": "What are Hazel eyes?",
  "response": "Hazel eyes are a unique eye color characterized by a combination of green, brown, and sometimes gold or amber tones. The appearance of hazel eyes can vary significantly depending on lighting conditions and the clothing or makeup a person is wearing. The color can range from light to dark, and hazel eyes may have a more dominant green or brown hue. \n\nThe distinct feature of hazel eyes is their ability to change color or appear to shift shades, which adds to their allure. This eye color is the result of a combination of different pigments and the way light scatters in the iris. Hazel eyes are relatively rare compared to other eye colors like brown or blue, and they are often associated with a warm, vibrant look.",
